<h2>pkmon: Least-Squares Estimator under k-Monotony Constraint for Discrete
Functions</h2>
<p>We implement two least-squares estimators under k-monotony constraint using a method based on the Support Reduction Algorithm from Groeneboom et al (2008) &lt;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1111%2Fj.1467-9469.2007.00588.x">doi:10.1111/j.1467-9469.2007.00588.x</a>&gt;. The first one is a projection estimator on the set of k-monotone discrete functions. The second one is a projection on the set of k-monotone discrete probabilities. This package provides functions to generate samples from the spline basis from Lefevre and Loisel (2013) &lt;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1239%2Fjap%2F1378401239">doi:10.1239/jap/1378401239</a>&gt;, and from mixtures of splines.</p>
